title: VLSI PD Lab
description: Lightweight VLSI physical design study notes with concise guides, checklists, and path-based learning.
permalink: /
priority: 1.0
---
<section class="hero shell">
  <div>
    <p class="eyebrow">Fast-loading test site | distinct from .top</p>
    <h1>VLSI Physical Design Lab Notes</h1>
    <p class="lede">This `.site` version uses a compact guide-and-track structure, shorter editorial copy, and minimal assets so it loads faster and does not mirror the `.top` site page-for-page.</p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/guides/">Browse Guides</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/tracks/">Open Study Tracks</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <aside class="hero-card" aria-label="How this site differs">
    <h2>What changed</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Different site name and metadata (`VLSI PD Lab`)</li>
      <li>New information architecture (`/guides` and `/tracks`)</li>
      <li>Short checklist-driven notes instead of mirrored long articles</li>
      <li>Lightweight CSS and no heavy UI JavaScript</li>
    </ul>
  </aside>
</section>

<section class="shell section">
  <div class="section-head">
    <h2>Guide Categories</h2>
    <p>{{ topics | length }} compact notes organized for quick study sessions.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="category-grid">
    {% for category in categories %}
    <article class="panel">
      <h3><a href="/guides/#{{ category.slug }}">{{ category.title }}</a></h3>
      <p>{{ category.description }}</p>
      <ul class="mini-list">
        {% for topic in topics %}
          {% if topic.category == category.slug %}
        <li><a href="/guides/{{ topic.slug }}/">{{ topic.title }}</a></li>
          {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="shell section">
  <div class="section-head">
    <h2>Study Tracks</h2>
    <p>Use a sequence if you want faster progress than random browsing.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="track-grid">
    {% for track in tracks %}
    <article class="panel">
      <h3><a href="/tracks/{{ track.slug }}/">{{ track.title }}</a></h3>
      <p>{{ track.description }}</p>
      <p class="meta">{{ track.steps | length }} steps</p>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="shell section">
  <div class="section-head">
    <h2>SEO Separation Note</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="callout">
    <p>The `.site` test domain intentionally uses a different layout, shorter copy, and different URL paths than `.top` so search engines do not see it as a mirrored version of the production site.</p>
  </div>
</section>
